# UX Research from Existing Games

| Example game/app | Target user | Colours/background | Icons/buttons | How it holds attention | Feedback/reward system | What we will apply |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Interland (Reality River)** | 7-12 years | Bright blues/purples, floating river islands. | Shields, "Stop" signs, simple arrows. | Simple arrows. Fast-paced movement and visual puzzles. | Immediate "Correct!" sounds and progress bars. | Using a "river" or "path" visual to show progress. |
| **The Phisherman** | Primary school | Underwater village, cartoon sea life. | Cartoon sea life. Fish hooks (threats), bubbles, trophies. | Mini-games focused on specific phishing types. | Post-game questions and discussion points. | Using "red flags" as visual icons to highlight scams. |
